    "content": "Thanks Lea. Your CSS guidance arrived after implementation was already underway, but I want to confirm the implementation matches your recommendations exactly:\n\n1. **Template**: \"Waiting For\" radio added after \"Project\" -- check. Waiting-for fields container with labeled input added after project-fields -- check. One small difference: the label text is \"Who or what are you waiting on?\" (slightly more descriptive than just \"Who or what?\") and placeholder is \"Who or what?\" -- this was per Steve Krug's UX guidance from the design phase.\n\n2. **Context field visibility**: Used your recommended **Option A** -- single `:has()` rule to hide `.inbox-item__shared-fields` when waiting_for radio is checked. Exactly as you specified.\n\n3. **CSS additions**: All styles match your proposed rules exactly -- progressive disclosure via `:has()`, waiting-for-fields hidden by default with `display: none`, shown as `display: flex` when selected, label and input styles mirror the existing first-action field patterns.\n\n4. **Progressive enhancement**: Backend handles empty `waiting_on` gracefully -- returns 204 (HTMX) or redirect (non-HTMX), item stays in inbox. Same pattern as project's empty first_action_title handling.\n\nThe implementation is ready for your review. All code is on disk (not yet committed). Would you like to examine any specific files?"
  }
